content.description: Start as far back in the overhang section as possible.  Usually the furthest back is seeping with water.  Bring some Chalk to dry out a key thin rail that tends to be moist.  Work a cruxy, possibly inverted, sequence to climb out of the over hang onto nice jugs and Top out.  Until the top of the boulder is cleaned up a bit more you climb right back down to your pad for a descent.
content.location: This climb starts under the obvious overhanging end of the boulder.

content.description: Sit start with feet under boulder.  There is another smaller part of the over hang right of Moon Jelly top out. Start on a left hand 2-3 finger pocket with a right hand 1-2 finger pocket.  Nice little 3-4 move problem. Top out is mossy on sharp rock. Down climb to climbers left where moon jelly tops out.

This boulder sits very near to Cam's Wall about 50 yards past Windy Point. You will likely notice the long bloc looking formation from the entry side and as you turn around the corner it will become obvious you are where you want to be.  There is room for a fun traverse and possibly some other sit start climbs along the length of the boulder.  This rock is also nice an sharp.
